{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Scope","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"ParentState"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"ParentAction","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Child","kind":"genericParameter"},{"kind":"text","text":"> "},{"text":"where","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Child"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:22ComposableArchitecture7ReducerP","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Reducer"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope","type":"reference"},{"text":" allows you to transform a parent domain into a child domain, and then run a child","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"reduce on that subset domain. This is an important tool for breaking down large features into","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"smaller units and then piecing them together. The smaller units can be easier to understand and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"test, and can even be packaged into their own isolated modules.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You hand "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" 3 pieces of data for it to do its job:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A writable key path that identifies the child state inside the parent state."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A case path that identifies the child actions inside the parent actions."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A @","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/ReducerBuilder","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" closure that describes the reducer you want to run on the child domain.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When run, it will intercept all child actions sent and feed them to the child reducer so that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"it can update the parent state and execute effects."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, given the basic scaffolding of child reducer:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Reducer","struct Child {","  struct State {","    \/\/ ...","  }","  enum Action {","    \/\/ ...","  }","  \/\/ ...","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A parent reducer with a domain that holds onto the child domain can use"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope\/init(state:action:child:)-88vdx","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" to embed the child reducer in its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer\/body-20w8t","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"code":["@Reducer","struct Parent {","  struct State {","    var child: Child.State","    \/\/ ...","  }","","  enum Action {","    case child(Child.Action)","    \/\/ ...","  }","","  var body: some Reducer<State, Action> {","    Scope(state: \\.child, action: \\.child) {","      Child()","    }","    Reduce { state, action in","      \/\/ Additional parent logic and behavior","    }","  }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Enum-state","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Enum state"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope"},{"type":"text","text":" reducer also works when state is modeled as an enum, not just a struct. In that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"case you can use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope\/init(state:action:child:fileID:filePath:line:column:)-9g44g"},{"text":" to specify a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"case path that identifies the case of state you want to scope to.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, if your state was modeled as an enum for unloaded\/loading\/loaded, you could"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"scope to the loaded case to run a reduce on only that case:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@Reducer","struct Feature {","  enum State {","    case unloaded","    case loading","    case loaded(Child.State)","  }","  enum Action {","    case child(Child.Action)","    \/\/ ...","  }","","  var body: some Reducer<State, Action> {","    Scope(state: \\.loaded, action: \\.child) {","      Child()","    }","    Reduce { state, action in","      \/\/ Additional feature logic and behavior","    }","  }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It is important to note that the order of combine ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and your additional feature logic"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"matters. It must be combined before the additional logic. In the other order it would be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"possible for the feature to intercept a child action, switch the state to another case, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"then the scoped child reducer would not be able to react to that action. That can cause subtle"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"bugs, and so we show a runtime warning in that case, and cause test failures.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For an alternative to using "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" with state case paths that enforces the order, check out"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope\/ifCaseLet(_:action:then:fileID:filePath:line:column:)-rdrb","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" operator."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Struct-state","identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope\/init(state:action:child:)-88vdx"],"title":"Struct state"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope\/init(state:action:child:fileID:filePath:line:column:)-9g44g"],"title":"Enum state","anchor":"Enum-state"},{"anchor":"Deprecations","title":"Deprecations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/ScopeDeprecations"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope\/reduce(into:action:)"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Methods","title":"Instance Methods"},{"title":"Default Implementations","anchor":"Default-Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/